header.gameNote: LAS VEGAS CLASSIC AT LAS VEGAS NV

article.headline: Kennesaw State 67, Maryland-Eastern Shore 49
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Shuan Stegall had 20 points and 11 rebounds, and Kennesaw State beat Maryland-Eastern Shore 67-49 Friday in the third round of the Las Vegas Classic. Andre Morgan had 13 points and three steals and Ronell Wooten added 12 points and five assists for the Owls (3-8), who took the lead for good by scoring the first eight points of the second half to snap a 27-27 tie. Kennesaw State wound up outscoring the Hawks 40-22 after halftime. Antonio McMillon led Maryland-Eastern Shore (1-8) with 13 points and 15 rebounds. Ed Tyson added 13 points for the Hawks -- all but three in the first half. The difference was at the foul line, where Kennesaw State shot 23-of-35 while Maryland-Eastern Shore was a miserable 4-of-17. Neither team fared well from beyond the arc, with Kennesaw State going 2-of-20 and Maryland-Eastern Shore shooting 3-of-14. The Hawks led by as many as seven points in the first half before the Owls went on a 14-7 run to finish the half, tying the game for the final time.
